STEVE NJUGUNA
A Nakuru-based human rights activist has been charged in a Nyahururu court with stealing from a police station.
When he appeared before Nyahururu Senior Resident Magistrate Njeri Mwangi, the activist, Mr Robert Njenga, denied two counts of stealing three trees.
It was alleged that on December 14, 2020 at Kabazi Police Station in Nakuru County, jointly with others who were not before the court, he stole two blue gum trees and an acacia tree, all valued at Sh23,598 which was the property of Kenya Police Service.



