He faced an alternative count of handling stolen items.
On December 15, 2020 in Kabazi area in Nakuru County, he was allegedly found with two blue gum trees valued at Sh22,112 that were believed to be stolen goods.
Mr Njenga has, however, accused some unidentified officers at the station of framing him for allegedly fighting impunity at the police station.



